                "name": "Slime Strand",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A leopard slug can turn its mucus into a 30-foot-long strand, much like a spider\u2019s silk. It can hang from this strand indefinitely and lower itself safely at a rate of 5 feet per round. It can climb back up the strand at the same rate. Once the slug breaks contact with the strand, the mucus disintegrates in 1d4 rounds."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Suction",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A leopard slug secretes sticky mucus, which allows it to apply its climb speed to any surface, even sheer walls and ceilings. Once attached to a surface, it has no chance of falling off unless it\u2019s grappled and actively peeled away."
